The drugs were concealed in a Corsa bakkie travelling between Mozambique and South Africa. JOHANNESBURG Heroin valued at R7 million has been discovered at the Lebombo boarder post. South African Revenue Service (Sars) officials say sniffer dogs led officials to a stash. The drugs were concealed in a Corsa bakkie travelling between Mozambique and South Africa. Sars spokesperson Janine Mqulwana says, The drugs were concealed inside the panels of a Corsa bakkie en route to South Africa from Mozambique. Twenty-five parcels of heroin weighing 26.6kg were found.